Step 1: Calculate the Gross Profit Margin.  
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
• From the income statement:  
 – Gross Profit = 4142813.42  
 – Total Revenue = 14542813.42  
• Computation:  
 4142813.42 / 14542813.42 ≈ 0.2850  
 0.2850 × 100 = 28.50%  

Step 2: Calculate the Cash Flow to Debt Ratio.  
• Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Total Liabilities)  
• From the cash flow statement:  
 – Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -17417367.15  
• From the balance sheet:  
 – Total Current Liabilities = 727140.68 (here, total liabilities are represented by Taxes Payable as Accounts Payable is 0)  
• Computation:  
 -17417367.15 / 727140.68 ≈ -23.96  

Thus, the final solution is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "28.50%",
    "Cash Flow to Debt Ratio": "-23.96"
  }
}
